                              <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                Do you often find yourself over analysing every single thing in your mind? I have had the habit of overthinking everything, literally everything. Sometimes, I would feel like my mind would burst like a pressure cooker waiting to explode at any moment ;) Based on my experiences and personal research, I have curated a few techniques that can help you get better at breaking the loop of intrusive thoughts. These steps include: practicing mindfulness, analysing your thoughts, following the "control chart", excellence over perfection, drawing the "yes or no" grid, diverting your thoughts, allotting a "worry time", and seeking professional help.

                                </p>
                               

                             
<br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">1. <u>Practice Mindfulness: 
                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                        
                            To be mindful, eliminate unnecessary thoughts and live in the present moment. Here's a quick and simple exercise that you can practice every day to practice mindfulness. All it takes is 5 minutes of your time. Repeat this cycle 5 to 6 times. During this process, you will reduce a thousand thoughts into two- 'inhale' and 'exhale'.
                        </p>
                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 1% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            <b>Step 1: Inhale for 5 seconds
                            </b>
                        </p>
                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 1% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            <b>Step 2: Hold your breath for 5 seconds

                            </b>
                        </p>
                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 1% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            <b>Step 3: Exhale slowly for 5 seconds

                            </b>
                        </p>
