                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">4. <u>Excellence over Perfection: </u>

                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            Perfectionism often becomes an obstacle in completing tasks and can lead to overthinking. Change your aim from completing tasks perfectly to getting the job done first. For example, while learning a chapter, instead of focusing on one section perfectly, focus on completing the entire chapter first and then revising. This will help prevent further worries about finishing the chapter. 
                        </p>

                        <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">5. <u>The "Yes or No" Grid: 


                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            This grid is a great tool to sort out the problems you need to stop worrying about and help you narrow down your concerns. You can tick down the yes or no columns and eliminate all unnecessary thoughts. 
